        </div>
    </div>
</div>
                        
                        <p>“It was profoundly better than I expected,” freshman Cullen Tyndall said. “A lot of what she said hit home in a lot of ways.”</p>
<p>The event was co-sponsored by Delta Gamma Sorority, which helped bring Maya Angelou to speak to the freshman class for the first time in 1994.</p>
<p>Senior Candice Nelson, who said she “snuck in” to hear Harris-Perry, said the message allowed her to both reflect on her time at Duke and look ahead.</p>
<p>“I thought she brought up some interesting points I had never considered,” Nelson said. “It made me think of ways I could make the most of my last year here.”</p>
<p class="p1"></p>

